{
  "texts": [
    "Laboratory automation has been commercially available for many years and, similar to industrial robots, it allows for tasks to be completed without user intervention.",
    "Total laboratory automation is an effective mean to eliminate batch processing delays and achieve a consistent and reliable laboratory service [77].A different type of service robots that has already been proven to be effective are pharmacy dispensing robots [63,64].",
    "Dispensing machines provide computer-controlled dispensing and tracking of medications.",
    "They decrease the potential for administration errors, and save nursing and pharmacists' time by eliminating the need for manual narcotic counts and inventory management.",
    "These robots have shown significant increases in pharmacy storage capacity, and a decrease in dispensing errors and time required to pick items for dispensing [59].Another relevant application of service robots includes sanitation robots, such as a climbing robot to clean hospital walls using disinfecting liquids [59], and a mobile platforms with arrays of ultraviolet (UV) lamps used to disinfect patient rooms and operating theatres [70,71]."
  ]
}